Meru Senator Mithika Linturi has been charged with attempted rape. Appearing at the Milimani Law Courts on Tuesday, Linturi was charged that on January 30, 2021 he attempted to rape a 36-year-old woman at Maiyan Villas Hotel in Nanyuki at around 3am. He further faced a second charge of committing an indecent act with an adult contrary to section 11(A) of the Sexual Offences Act. He pleaded not guilty to both counts before Magistrate Nanzushi and was released on a cash bail of Ksh.200,000. The case will be mentioned on October 26. Also Read: Video Of The Day: Iconic city hotels staring at bleak future